cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CC 

The paper discusses game theory and computational restrictions when modeling agents, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.GT (Game Theory) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a notion of equilibrium in the context of machine games, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also presents techniques for establishing equilibria and results on the structure of equilibria, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the simplification of strategies, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
